// MarkdownPreview
// Renders markdown content to HTML using ReactMarkdown with full custom
// component overrides. Supports inline diff highlighting (added/removed text),
// image resolution from design/diagram IDs, annotation rendering, collapsible
// sections, and syntax-highlighted code blocks.

Image sources are resolved from @design/id, @diagram/id, ./designs/id, and
./diagrams/id patterns to API endpoint URLs.
Diff mode computes a character-level LCS diff between old and new content and
colors added/removed segments inline.

FUNCTION computeLCS(a, b) -> number[][]
  Builds an O(m*n) DP table and returns the LCS length matrix.

---

FUNCTION computeLineDiff(oldLine, newLine) -> DiffSegment[]
  Calls computeLCS on the character arrays of both lines.
  Backtracks the LCS table to produce a list of {type, text} segments:
  "added" (in new only), "removed" (in old only), or "unchanged".

---

FUNCTION resolveImageSrc(src) -> string
  Maps @design/id and ./designs/id to /api/designs/:id/export?format=png.
  Maps @diagram/id and ./diagrams/id to /api/diagrams/:id/export?format=png.
  Returns src unchanged for all other values.

---

FUNCTION MarkdownPreview(content, oldContent, collapsibleSections, ...) -> JSX  EXPORT
  CALLS: CollapsibleMarkdown (CollapsibleMarkdown), CollapsibleDetails (CollapsibleDetails)
  Builds a components map overriding all standard markdown elements:
    h1-h6: styled headings
    p, strong, em, a: inline text styles
    img: calls resolveImageSrc before rendering
    ul, ol, li: list styles
    pre: SyntaxHighlighter (detects language from code fence info string)
    code: inline code style
    blockquote, hr: decorative styles
    table/thead/tbody/tr/td/th: table styles
    annotation: dispatches to AnnotationRenderer with type/index props
    details/summary: maps to CollapsibleDetails/CollapsibleSummary
  IF collapsibleSections: wraps in CollapsibleMarkdown.
  ELSE: renders ReactMarkdown directly.
  IF diff mode (oldContent provided): shows DiffControls banner above content.
